com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class ContentSwapperListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.ContentSwapperListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener

    public class ContentSwapperListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    This listener can be used to swap a rendition and primary content on a node. The usual use case would be if a document has primary content of type msw8 (MS Word) and a PDF rendition. The content swapper listener can be used to swap the rendition into the primary content, and make the old primary content a rendition. It can optionally also drop the existing primary content off of the node after the swap has been performed using the deleteAfterSwap injectable.
